<p><em>Brian Sholis interviewed me on <a href="https://magazine.frontier.is/p/drew-austin#details" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">his podcast</a> this week. We discussed how digital technology has affected our relationship to physical space, how cities have struggled to adapt, and what makes good public space. It’s short—less than 30 minutes—so give it a listen!</em></p><p>In August, Paul Graham <a href="https://twitter.com/paulg/status/1691678211011490291" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">tweeted</a> a pair of observations about downtown San Francisco, calling them “two visions of two possible futures of SF”:</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5182cf30-2b74-4834-8395-fdc735117fa9_1074x482.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ncHFc3GtmfCffDP1kX2QLlFMaaCg1UO06W8sNch_OAo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY1MTgyY2YzMC0yYjc0LTQ4MzQtODM5NS1mZGM3MzUxMTdmYTlfMTA3NHg0ODIucG5n 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Rt1eHs_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/QGanjUF_yTiEyzWRt3mC4BX1PBYtTWNnLtsM_YX8HyU=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGNTE4MmNmMzAtMmI3NC00ODM0LTgzOTUtZmRjNzM1MTE3ZmE5XzEwNzR4NDgyLnBuZw== 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/jxxyFstaG3at9Tor6T4x_2N43GOP_" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/N1yL28_0ap5tLTZJ